Interface ISignalOnTriggerExit2D

Namespace
Quantum
Assembly
Quantum.Simulation.dll

Interface for receiving callbacks once a non-trigger and a trigger 2D colliders stop touching. No collision is checked between two kinematic colliders that are both trigger or both non-trigger.At least one of the entities involved in a collision must have the respective Quantum.CallbackFlags set for the callback to be called.See Quantum.Physics2D.PhysicsEngine2D.Api.SetCallbacks(Quantum.EntityRef, Quantum.CallbackFlags) for setting the callbacks flags to an entity.
